  "local_port": 56542,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "About traffic rules?",
  "response": "Traffic rules are regulations designed to ensure the orderly and safe flow of vehicles and pedestrians on roads and highways. While specific traffic rules can vary by country or region, there are some common principles and rules that are widely observed around the world:\n\n1. **Traffic Signals and Signs:**\n   - Obey all traffic lights and signals (red means stop, green means go, and yellow means prepare to stop).\n   - Observe and adhere to all posted signs, such as stop signs, yield signs, and speed limits.\n\n2. **Speed Limits:**\n   - Follow posted speed limits, which can vary depending on the type of road and area (e.g., residential, urban, or highway).\n   - Adjust speed based on road conditions, weather, and visibility.\n\n3. **Right of Way:**\n   - Yield to pedestrians at crosswalks.\n   - At intersections, yield to vehicles already in the intersection or those coming from the right in countries with right-hand traffic, and left in countries with left-hand traffic unless otherwise directed.\n   - Emergency vehicles with active sirens or flashing lights always have the right of way.\n\n4. **Lanes and Lane Usage:**\n   - Follow lane markings and use designated lanes correctly (e.g., turning lanes, bike lanes).\n   - Do not change lanes abruptly and always signal when changing lanes.\n\n5. **Overtaking and Passing:**\n   - Pass on the appropriate side of a vehicle, which varies by country (usually the left in right-hand traffic countries and the right in left-hand traffic countries).\n   - Ensure it is safe to pass and not into oncoming traffic, particularly on two-lane roads.\n\n6. **Stopping and Parking:**\n   - Do not park in restricted areas or where your vehicle could obstruct traffic.\n   - Follow rules for parallel parking, angle parking, and other parking methods.\n   - Use hazard lights when parked at the side of the road in emergency situations.\n\n7. **Use of Indicators and Lights:**\n   - Use turn signals when turning or changing lanes.\n   - Headlights should be used in low visibility conditions, such as at night or during heavy rain.\n\n8. **Seat Belts and Safety:**\n   - All passengers must wear seat belts.\n   - Children should be in appropriate car seats or booster seats as required by law.\n\n9. **No Use of Mobile Devices:**\n   - Do not use mobile phones or other devices that can distract you while driving unless in hands-free mode.\n\n10. **Driving Under the Influence:**\n    - Strictly avoid driving under the influence of alcohol or drugs.\n\nTraffic rules are implemented not only for the safety of individual drivers but also for all road users. It's crucial for drivers to stay informed about local traffic laws and regulations. Always stay vigilant and defensive while driving, keeping the safety of everyone on the road as a priority.",
